# Evorise Mobile App — Full Native Rebuild Plan

> **Goal**: User should not be able to tell if it's a web app or a native app. Every page, every interaction, every component must look and feel like a premium native iOS/Android app.

---

## The Problem With Current Mobile UI

| Issue | Current State | Target State |
|---|---|---|
| **Layout** | Scaled-down desktop with padding changes | True mobile-first: cards, lists, bottom sheets |
| **Navigation** | Bottom tab bar exists but pages still look "web" | Every page has native-app page structure |
| **Header** | Generic title bar | iOS-style large title + sticky section headers |
| **Tables** | CSS-transformed table rows | Replaced with native list cells (like Contacts app) |
| **Forms** | Desktop modal overlays | Bottom sheet forms with grouped iOS inputs |
| **Data density** | Cramped desktop data forced into small screen | Context-appropriate mobile information hierarchy |
| **Touch targets** | Mix of small and large tap areas | All tap targets ≥ 44px, proper spacing |
| **Animations** | None / web-style | Spring animations, slide-in sheets, haptic-like feedback |
| **Empty states** | Generic text | Illustrated, friendly empty states |
| **FAB** | Only on some pages | Every page that needs creation has proper FAB |

---

## Architecture Decisions

### Strategy: `isMobile` branch — separate JSX trees
Every component already has `if (isMobile) { return <MobileUI />; }` pattern.
**We keep this and rebuild the `<MobileUI />` tree for every single component from scratch.**

### Design System: "Evorise App" — iOS-inspired but branded
- Background: `#F2F2F7` (iOS system grouped background)
- Cards: `#FFFFFF` with `border-radius: 12px`
- Primary Blue: `#0066CC` (Evorise brand ocean blue)
- Accent Orange: `#FF6820` (Evorise deep orange)
- iOS system colors for status: `#34C759` green, `#FF3B30` red, `#FF9500` amber
- Typography: `-apple-system` font stack, 34px large title, 17px body, 13px caption
- Dividers: `0.5px solid #C6C6C8` (native thin separator)

### New CSS Classes in `mobile-app.css`
All new native patterns live in dedicated CSS classes, NOT inline styles.

---

## Page-by-Page Rebuild Plan

### PHASE 1 — Foundation & Core App Shell (App.jsx + CSS)

**App.jsx Mobile Shell:**
- [x] Existing: bottom nav bar, app bar, more sheet *(functional but needs polish)*
- [ ] **Fix**: App bar needs dynamic "large title" mode that collapses on scroll (like iOS)
- [ ] **Fix**: Bottom nav needs haptic-style active state (scale + color fill)
- [ ] **Fix**: "More" sheet needs grid layout (3-column icon grid) instead of list items
- [ ] **New**: Page transition animations (slide-in from right for sub-pages)
- [ ] **New**: Pull-to-refresh visual indicator

**CSS Layer — New Native Classes:**
- `.mob-large-title` — 34px bold, collapses on scroll
- `.mob-section-header` — iOS section header (gray cap, 13px uppercase)
- `.mob-inset-group` — white card container with 12px radius
- `.mob-cell` — individual list row (64px min, with separator)
- `.mob-cell-icon` — 40px rounded icon leading
- `.mob-cell-trailing` — chevron / badge / switch trailing
- `.mob-page` — full height page container
- `.mob-segment` — iOS-style segmented control
- `.mob-search-bar` — native rounded search input
- `.mob-empty-state` — centered icon + message
- `.mob-action-btn` — full-width primary action button
- `.mob-sheet` — already exists, needs spring animation
- `.mob-badge-dot` — notification dot on icons

