### PHASE 2 — Dashboard (Dashboard.jsx)

**Current**: Grid stat cards, quick action buttons, recent task list
**Target**: True iOS Home Screen / Dashboard App feel

**Layout:**
```
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│ Good morning, Rahim     🔔  │  ← Large title header
│ Tuesday, July 15            │
├─────────────────────────────┤
│ [Pending] [Done] [Team] [Cli]│  ← Horizontal scroll stat pills
├─────────────────────────────┤
│ ⚡ QUICK ACTIONS             │  ← Section header
│ [My Day] [Tasks] [Chat] [+] │  ← 4-column app icon grid
├─────────────────────────────┤
│ 📋 RECENT TASKS             │  ← Section header
│ ○ Task Name          High → │  ← Native list cells
│ ✓ Completed Task     Done   │
│ ○ Another Task       Med  → │
├─────────────────────────────┤
│ 👥 TEAM OVERVIEW            │  ← Admin only section
│ [Avatar] Name  8 tasks →    │
└─────────────────────────────┘
```

**Key changes:**
- Stats become a horizontal scroll strip of colored pill cards (like Apple Watch stats)
- Quick actions become proper app icon grid (icon + label under it)
- Task list uses `.mob-inset-group` with `.mob-cell` rows
- Section headers use `.mob-section-header` pattern

